    <text id="F0921T">

        <front id="d2">

            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">

                <p>Suggests that oaths of allegiance to the Union should be administered.</p>

            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">

            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Thaddeus Stevens</name>
                </head>
                <opener>

                    <dateline>

                        <date value="1862-03-20">Thursd. March 20/62</date>
                        <name type="place">Mercersburg Penna</name>

                    </dateline>

                    <salute>Hon. T. Stevens<lb/> Dear Sir,</salute>

                </opener>



                <p>Can there not, <hi rend="underline">in some way</hi> a provision be made, <hi
                        rend="underline">requiring at once, or very soon an oath of every person in
                        the land</hi> -- that no oath, past, or future, to any society, <hi
                        rend="underline">Secret</hi>, or open shall be <hi rend="underline">as</hi>
                    obligatory, as that to support the State &amp; National Laws, &amp;
                    Government.</p>



                <p>I am thoroughly persuaded, that <hi rend="underline">most</hi> persons, <hi
                        rend="underline">because</hi> they have never taken an oath to support the
                    State &amp; National Laws &amp; Government, believe themselves to be
                    under more solemn obligations to support that organization &amp; it laws, to
                    which they <hi rend="underline">have</hi> given their oaths. I have never taken
                    an oath to any Secret Society, least my conscience, <hi rend="underline"
                        >perverted</hi>, might cause me to sin. Such oaths, I fear, have had <hi
                        rend="underline">much</hi> to do with this <hi rend="underline"
                    >Rebellion</hi>; and <hi rend="underline">will have</hi> power, greatly
                    injurious, in settling terms with <hi rend="underline">traitors</hi>.</p>



                <closer>

                    <salute>Very Respectfully Yours,</salute>

                    <signed>John R. Agnew</signed>

                </closer>

            </div1>

        </body>

    </text>

